        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "My soul is bowed down - The Septuagint, the Vulgate, and Luther render this in the plural, and in the active form: \"They have bowed down my soul;\" that is, they have caused my soul to be bowed down. The Hebrew may be correctly rendered, \"he pressed down my soul,\" - referring to his enemies, and speaking of them in the singular number.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They have digged a pit before me ... - See Psalm 7:15-16, notes; Psalm 9:15, note; Job 5:13, note. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "They have digged a pit before me ... - See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
